abstract: >-
  Chaeshin is a persistent memory layer for tool-using LLM agents based on
  case-based reasoning. Each case stores a Tool Graph; nodes can themselves
  unfold into child cases, giving a graph-of-graphs structure with no fixed
  decomposition depth. Outcomes are tri-state (success / failure / pending),
  with success and failure transitions reserved for an explicit user verdict.
  Editing a parent layer's graph cascades to descendants — children whose
  anchor node was removed are automatically flipped back to pending for
  review. Ships with an MCP server for Claude Code integration, a Next.js
  observability monitor, and ReAct demos for cooking, lifestyle coaching,
  and clinical intake domains.
